Flashcard Quiz App

📌 Project Overview

The Flashcard Quiz App is a simple and interactive Python application developed using Tkinter. It helps users study and memorize information through digital flashcards. Each flashcard contains a question on the front and an answer on the back.

Users can easily navigate through flashcards, reveal answers, and manage their own flashcard collection by adding, editing, or deleting cards.

✨ Features

- Display questions on flashcards
- Show answers with a single click
- Navigate using Next and Previous buttons
- Add new flashcards
- Edit existing flashcards
- Delete unwanted flashcards
- User-friendly graphical interface
- Automatic data storage using JSON files

🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- Tkinter (GUI Library)
- JSON (Data Storage)

🚀 How to Run

1. Install Python on your system.
2. Download the project files.
3. Open the project folder in VS Code.
4. Run the following command:

python flashcard_quiz_app.py

📂 Project Structure

FlashcardQuizApp/
│
├── flashcard_quiz_app.py
├── flashcards.json
└── README.md

🎯 Learning Outcomes

- Python GUI Development using Tkinter
- Working with JSON files
- CRUD Operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- Event Handling in Python
- Building Interactive Applications

📸 Output

The application provides a clean and simple interface where users can create, manage, and review flashcards efficiently.

